          </li>
          <li>
            <svg role="img" aria-label="Kubernetes" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 722.8 702"><path style="fill:#326ce5" transform="translate(-6 -175)" d="M365 185a47 46 0 0 0-18 4L103 306a47 46 0 0 0-25 32L18 600a47 46 0 0 0 6 35 47 46 0 0 0 3 4l169 210a47 46 0 0 0 36 18h271a47 46 0 0 0 37-18l169-210a47 46 0 0 0 9-39l-60-263a47 46 0 0 0-26-31L388 189a47 46 0 0 0-23-4z"/><path style="fill:#fff" transform="translate(-6 -175)" d="M368 274c-8 0-15 7-15 16v4l2 14 2 27c-1 3-3 6-5 7v7a190 190 0 0 0-122 58l-6-3c-2 0-5 1-8-1l-20-18-10-10-3-3c-3-2-7-4-10-4-5 0-9 2-12 5-5 7-3 16 4 22l3 3 12 7 22 15c2 2 3 7 3 8l5 5c-26 37-37 84-30 131l-6 2c-2 2-4 6-7 7l-26 4-14 1-4 1c-9 2-14 10-13 18 2 8 11 12 19 11h1v-1h4l13-5c9-4 17-7 25-8l9 3 6-1c15 45 45 82 84 105l-2 7c1 2 2 5 1 8l-13 24-8 11-2 4c-4 8-1 18 6 21 8 4 17 0 20-8l2-4 5-13c3-10 6-20 11-27l6-3 3-6a189 189 0 0 0 135 1l4 5c2 1 5 2 7 5l10 24 4 14 2 4c4 8 13 11 20 8 8-4 10-13 7-21l-2-4-8-12c-6-8-10-15-13-23-1-4 0-6 1-8l-2-6c40-24 70-62 84-106l6 1c2-2 4-4 8-3 8 1 16 4 26 7l13 5 4 1c9 2 17-3 19-10 2-8-4-16-12-18l-5-1-14-1c-10-1-18-2-26-5-3-1-5-5-6-6l-6-2a189 189 0 0 0-31-131l6-5c0-3 0-5 2-8 6-6 13-10 22-16l12-7 4-2c7-6 8-16 3-22s-15-7-22-1l-3 2-10 11c-7 7-13 13-19 17-3 2-7 2-9 1l-6 4c-31-33-75-54-121-58v-7c-2-2-5-3-5-7-1-8 0-16 1-27l2-14v-4c0-9-6-16-14-16zm-19 113-4 77a13 13 0 0 1-21 10l-63-44a151 151 0 0 1 88-43zm37 0c33 5 64 20 88 43l-63 44a13 13 0 0 1-21-10zm-148 71 58 52a13 13 0 0 1-5 22l-74 22c-4-35 4-68 21-96zm259 0a153 153 0 0 1 22 95l-74-21a13 13 0 0 1-5-22h-1l58-52zm-141 56h23l15 18-5 23-21 10-21-10-6-23zm75 62h3l77 13c-12 32-33 59-61 77l-30-72a13 13 0 0 1 11-18zm-128 1a13 13 0 0 1 12 18l-29 71c-27-18-49-44-61-77l76-12h2zm64 31c2-1 4 0 6 1 3 1 5 3 6 5l38 68a154 154 0 0 1-98-1l37-67c3-4 7-6 11-6z"/></svg>
          </li>
          <li>
            <svg role="img" aria-label="GitHub" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor"><path d="M12 .297c-6.63 0-12 5.373-12 12 0 5.303 3.438 9.8 8.205 11.385.6.113.82-.258.82-.577 0-.285-.01-1.04-.015-2.04-3.338.724-4.042-1.61-4.042-1.61-.546-1.387-1.333-1.756-1.333-1.756-1.089-.745.083-.729.083-.729 1.205.084 1.839 1.237 1.839 1.237 1.07 1.834 2.807 1.304 3.492.997.107-.775.418-1.305.762-1.604-2.665-.305-5.467-1.334-5.467-5.931 0-1.311.469-2.381 1.236-3.221-.124-.303-.535-1.524.117-3.176 0 0 1.008-.322 3.301 1.23a11.51 11.51 0 0 1 3.003-.404c1.018.005 2.045.138 3.003.404 2.291-1.552 3.297-1.23 3.297-1.23.653 1.653.242 2.874.118 3.176.77.84 1.235 1.911 1.235 3.221 0 4.609-2.807 5.624-5.479 5.921.43.372.823 1.102.823 2.222 0 1.606-.014 2.898-.014 3.293 0 .321.218.694.825.576C20.565 22.092 24 17.592 24 12.297c0-6.627-5.373-12-12-12"/></svg>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Governance -->
      <section id="governance" class="section sec-a">
        <h2>Governance</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          The Data Privacy Stack follows a <strong>Minimum Viable Governance (MVG)</strong>
          model, a lightweight, two-tier structure that puts clear, consensus-based
          governance in place without heavyweight overhead.
        </p>
        <div class="cards">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Technical Steering Committee</h3>
            <p>At the organization level, the TSC sets overall direction and coordinates
              across projects: technical roadmap, maintainer appointments, and governance
              policy.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Project Maintainers</h3>
            <p>Each project is run by its maintainers through a lightweight,
              consensus-based process, reviewing contributions and keeping the project
              secure, maintained, and modern.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="more">
          The authoritative governance documents (charter, code of conduct, steering
          committee, and per-project governance) live in the
          <a href={mvgRepo}>MVG repository</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Blog -->
      <section id="blog" class="section sec-b">
        <h2>Blog</h2>
        <p class="lead">News, releases, and notes from the community.</p>
        <ul class="posts">
          {posts.map((post) => (
            <li>
              <a href={`/${postKey(post)}/`}>{post.data.title}</a>
              {post.data.description && <span class="post-desc">{post.data.description}</span>}
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Community -->
